content.rendered:
I haven’t finished with my building; I’d love to photograph everyone who lives there. And probably will. But I found myself in the mood for a change of scene, so ventured beyond for this week’s square portrait.

I’d met Rachel once, through a friend, before going to her 14th floor London Fields flat to make this picture. Rachel’s a community mediator and massage therapist, and she explores the intersections between these and other fields and their wider context on her blog.
